You lucky devil.
I have a 486dx2/66 with S3805 VL Bus based card (quadtel Brand with Phoenix BIOS)
that has worked perfectly for years. Warp install recognised it as an S3 card but
configured it incorrectly though. I can recommend S3 based cards.

For a sound card you can't go past a Media Vision PAS16. Native support under
OS2 and you can use the Sound Blaster side for DOS and WIN/OS2 (a little tricky to
set up but plenty of support available here).

I use and recommend Adaptec SCSI also with native support. I have three hard drives
and a Colorado Powertape QIC drive attached and have never had a problem.

I also have a NEC double spin SCSI CDROM attached to the SCSI controller on the
Media Vision Sound Card (had to download the SCSI driver but it works great).

I also had a noname 14.4K modem that had problems (dropping out after 20 mins)
and replaced it with a Hayes Optima 28.8K that works like a dream.
Also I would suggest getting 16550 UARTS on your coms ports.

